properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 18 at 7:40PM AKST until January 19 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches.
Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Southern Inner Channels including the Ketchikan area.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM AKST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions are found, especially
Point Higgins north and from Mountain Point up George's Inlet.
Power outages occurred earlier in the day, per multiple reports
in Ketchikan. According to local media, a barge and a wooden
boat went aground on the Bar Harbor breakwater earlier in the
day.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Up to 2 inches of snow was falling in a
three hour period at times during the event. Snow amounts of a
trace to 4 inches have been reported in Downtown Ketchikan with
intermittent mixing to rain. North of Ketchikan, 3 to 8 inches
of snow have been reported. In Saxman, around 2 to 4 inches have
been reported. From Mountain Point up George's Inlet around 7
inches have been reported.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST SUNDAY
